
[1]dissuasive

   DISSUASIVE, a. Tending to dissuade, or divert form a measure or
   purpose; dehortatory.

   DISSUASIVE, n. Reason, argument, or counsel, employed to deter one from
   a measure or purpose; that which is used or which tends to divert the
   mind from any purpose or pursuit. The consequences of intemperance are
   powerful dissuasives from indulging in that vice.
